Template: grub/install_grub
Type: boolean
Default: false
Description: Would you like to install the updated GRUB bootloader?
 The system bootloader (GRUB) components has been updated with new features
 and fixes. Therefore, it is recommended to upgrade the GRUB bootloader
 installed on your master boot record (MBR), EFI system partition (ESP), and
 other forms of firmware boot partitions.
 .
 However, if you have complex partition schemes, such as having the boot
 partition (/boot) on a RAID array or encrypted partitions (LUKS, etc.), it
 may be prudent to say "no" and install GRUB manually with the "grub-install"
 command. If you would like to use GRUB from another system distribution or
 use other bootloaders, you may also want to say "no" here.
Description-zh_CN.UTF-8: 您要安装更新后的 GRUB 引导器吗？
 系统引导器 (GRUB) 组件已更新，包含新特性和修复。因此，我们推荐您更新安装在
 主引导记录 (MBR)、EFI 系统分区 (ESP) 或其他固件引导分区上的 GRUB 引导器。
 .
 注意：如果您正在使用复杂分区配置，如在 RAID 阵列上存放引导分区 (/boot) 或正
 使用加密分区（如 LUKS），我们建议您在此选择“否”并使用 "grub-install" 手动
 安装 GRUB 引导器。如果您希望使用另外一个系统提供的 GRUB 或正使用其他引导器，
 我们也建议在此选择“否”。
